風格上，《超人氣》是一張明顯受20世紀80年代風格<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/f6bd/|title=Review of Lady GaGa – The Fame|first=Talia|last=Kraines|publisher=[[BBC_Music|BBC Music]]|accessdate=2017-07-05|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161227235901/http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/f6bd/|archivedate=2016-12-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/jan/09/lady-gaga-the-fame|title=Lady Gaga: The Fame|first=Alexis|last=Petridis|date=2009-01-08|work=The Guardian|accessdate=2017-07-05|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922145027/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/jan/09/lady-gaga-the-fame|archivedate=2013-09-22}}</ref>影響的[[電音流行|電音流行]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Plagenhoef|first=Scott|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/13823-the-fame-monster/|title=Lady Gaga: The Fame Monster|work=[[Pitchfork|Pitchfork]]|date=2010-01-13|accessdate=2016-02-20|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214143551/http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/13823-the-fame-monster/|archivedate=2016-02-14}}</ref>、[[合成器流行|合成器流行]] <ref>{{cite web|last=Matthew|first=Jennie|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-fame-mw0001327294|title=Lady Gaga launches new Artpop album with VIP party|work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|date=2013-11-11|accessdate=2017-07-11|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805075923/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/10440816/Lady-Gaga-launches-new-Artpop-album-with-VIP-party.html|archivedate=2017-08-05}}</ref>以及[[流行舞曲|流行舞曲]]專輯。<ref name="allmusic" />大部分收錄的歌曲像是《[[撲克臉_(女神卡卡歌曲)|撲克臉]]》(Poker Face) 、《[[舞力全開_(歌曲)|舞力全開]]》(Just Dance) 以及《[[愛情遊戲|愛情遊戲]]》(Love Game) 等皆是輕快的流行舞曲，其中《撲克臉》更是在[[副歌|副歌]]及Hook的部分加入了深沉的配樂及清澈的聲樂。<ref name=about.com>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/pokerface.htm|title=Lady GaGa – "Poker Face"|last=Lamb|first=Bill|date=2008-11-12|accessdate=2009-03-18|publisher=About.com|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090203163928/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/pokerface.htm|archivedate=2009-02-03}}</ref> 比起節拍較偏向舞曲風的《愛情遊戲》，《舞力全開》則更偏向電音風，而《金錢寶貝》(Money Honey) 則帶有穩重的電子[[旋|旋味]]。<ref name="Money Honey">{{cite web|title=Lady Gaga – Money Honey – Digital Sheet Music|publisher=Musicnotes.com}}</ref> 以上歌曲都結合了帶有輕快節拍的合成樂、並在削弱了[[電音|電音]]的部份的同時加入了當代[[節奏藍調|節奏藍調]]的鼓舞性節奏。<ref name="guardian">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/jan/09/lady-gaga-the-fame|title=Lady Gaga: The Fame|last=Petridis|first=Alexis|authorlink=Alexis Petridis|date=2009-01-09|work=[[衛報|衛報]]|accessdate=2009-04-28|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922145027/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/jan/09/lady-gaga-the-fame|archivedate=2013-09-22}}</ref> 其中《愛情狗仔》(Paparazzi) 加入了感性的節奏<ref name="popmatters">{{cite web|url=http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/68939-lady-gaga-the-fame/|title=Lady GaGa The Fame|last=Sawdey|first=Evan|date=2009-01-12|work=[[PopMatters|PopMatters]]|accessdate=2009-04-30|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327140058/http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/68939-lady-gaga-the-fame|archivedate=2009-03-27}}</ref> 而《夏日男孩》(Summerboy) 的風格則明顯受到樂團[[金髮美女|金髮美女]]的影響。<ref name="Electro Pop Diva">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1110125/Why-world-going-Gaga-electro-pop-diva-Stefani.html|title=Why The World Is Going Gaga For Electro-pop Diva Stefani|work=[[Daily_Mail|Daily Mail]]|first=Adrian|last=Thrills|date=2009-01-09|accessdate=2009-01-12|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5n9VafHne?url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1110125/Why-world-going-gaga-electro-pop-diva-Stefani.html|archivedate=2010-01-29}}</ref> 《[[嗯，嗯（無話可說）|嗯，嗯（無話可說）]]》(Eh, Eh (Nothing Else I Can Say)) 與其它《超人氣》的歌曲相比，則更類似於有著20世紀80年代風格的謠曲，<ref name="allmusic" /> <ref name="popmatters" /> 該曲同時也引用了蕾哈娜知名單曲《雨傘》(Umbrella (2007)) 中「誒，誒」聲的Hook。<ref name="washington">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/27/AR2008102702579.html|title='Fame' Isn't Worth Getting GaGa Over|last=du Lac|first=Freedom|date=2008-10-18|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|accessdate=2009-05-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110012432/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/27/AR2008102702579.html|archivedate=2012-11-10}}</ref>

歌詞上，《超人氣》的歌詞反映出了成名即獲得人氣；對於《撲克臉》中對性向的暗示及諷刺。<ref name=about.com /> 卡卡在英國小報《[[每日星報|每日星報]]》中解釋歌詞正是暗示著對性與愛的疑惑。<ref name="dailystar">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/playlist/view/75068/EXCLUSIVE-Lady-Gaga-s-hot-secret/|title=Lady Gaga's Hot Secret|first=Kim|last=Beysil|date=2009-04-01|work=[[Daily_Star_(United_Kingdom)|Daily Star]]|accessdate=2009-04-10|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091119051710/http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=UICS-9104|archivedate=2009-11-19}}</ref> 根據BBC的報導，歌曲中「Mum-mum-mum-mah」的Hook是擷取自[[波尼M合唱團|波尼M合唱團]]1997年的熱單《[[媽媽巴克|媽媽巴克]]》(Ma Baker) 。<ref name=bbcchartblog>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/chartblog/2009/03/lady_gaga_poker_face.shtml|title=Lady GaGa – 'Poker Face'|last=McAlpine|first=Fraser|date=2009-03-11|accessdate=2009-03-17|publisher=BBC News|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318054456/http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/chartblog/2009/03/lady_gaga_poker_face.shtml|archivedate=2009-03-18}}</ref> 以歌詞「舞池裡發生了什麼? / 我愛這旋律，但我已經無法直走<ref group="注">原文：「What's going on on the floor? / I love this record, baby but I can't see straight anymore」</ref>」為例，《舞力全開》描寫著在派對中逐漸醉暈。<ref name="avclub">{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/lady-gaga-the-fame,6744/|title=Lady Gaga:The Fame|last=Koski|first=Genevieve|date=2008-11-10|work=[[The_A.V._Club|The A.V. Club]]|accessdate=2009-04-28|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090916224422/http://www.avclub.com/articles/lady-gaga-the-fame%2C6744/|archivedate=2009-09-16}}</ref> 與作為專輯中心的概念相同，《愛情遊戲》描寫出愛、名氣及性向的議題。<ref name="heraldsun">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1206508/Lady-GaGa-goes-naked-kisses-woman-risque-new-video-LoveGame.html|title=It's kisses all round as Lady GaGa gets affectionate with men AND women in risqué new video|work=[[Daily_Mail|Daily Mail]]|date=2009-05-21|accessdate=2009-05-27|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120630023041/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1206508/Lady-GaGa-goes-naked-kisses-woman-risque-new-video-LoveGame.html|archivedate=2012-06-30}}</ref> 《愛情狗仔》在描寫著粉絲跟蹤著他最愛慕的名人的同時，<ref name="aboutreview">{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/od/reviews/fr/LadyGagaTheFame.htm|title=Lady Gaga – 'The Fame'|last=Norman|first=Ben|date=2008-10-02|publisher=About.com|accessdate=2009-04-17|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090502215806/http://dancemusic.about.com/od/reviews/fr/LadyGagaTheFame.htm|archivedate=2009-05-02}}</ref> 也描寫著渴望成名以及被閃光燈捕捉並成為焦點。<ref name="broward">{{cite news|url=http://www.browardpalmbeach.com/2009-04-02/music/some-like-it-pop/|title=Some Like It Pop|last=Hobart|first=Erika|date=2009-03-31|work=[[New_Times_Broward-Palm_Beach|New Times Broward-Palm Beach]]|accessdate=2009-04-30|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090422163227/http://www.browardpalmbeach.com/2009-04-02/music/some-like-it-pop|archivedate=2009-04-22}}</ref>

